songs.title: On My Way
songs.lyrics:
[Intro]
I don't know how I was so blind
You let me go every time
Thought it was all just in my mind
How could you leave my heart behind?
Trying not to let you go
But you hurt me more than you know
If you don't wanna show up for me
I'd rather just live my life alone

[Pre-Hook]
If I can't do much better
Yeah, that's what I tell myself
Every time I think about you
I done had enough, Of what you call love
Now that it's all up for ya

[Hook]
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay, toward you
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay, toward you
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay, toward you
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay

[Verse 2]
What do we do
Will we make it, I'll never know
What do we do
Will we do it babe
If I can't do much better
Yeah, that's what I tell myself
Every time I think about you
I done had enough, Of what you call love
Now that it's all up for ya

[Hook]
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay, toward you
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay, toward you
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay, toward you
I'll be on my way, ay, ay, ay

[Verse 3]
I can't do much better
Yeah, that's what I tell myself
I can't do much better
Every time I think about you
What do we do
Will we make it, I'll never know
What do we do
Will we do it babe

[Outro: Rio]
Yeah, I can't do much better
Yeah that's what I tell myself
I can't do much better
Every time I think about you
I can't do much better
Yeah that's what I tell myself
I can't do much better
Every time I think about you
